<paragraph id="8BDBE937FFBFC835FF47FE1FFD3A2160" blockId="5.[136,1452,410,1085]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFBFC835FE96FE1EFE4022BD" box="[345,507,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elisaeanum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFBFC835FE96FE1EFE4022BD" box="[345,507,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">H. elisaeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes a complete description in Latin, followed by the provenance and a mention of two gatherings: “In 
<collectingRegion id="49A027D5FFBFC835FE4FFE3BFE6322D1" box="[384,472,446,472]" country="Spain" name="Aragon" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Aragon</collectingRegion>
. australi (Sierra de Javalambre ad rup. calcar. alt. 
<quantity id="4C9C44D2FFBFC835FC32FE3BFBE822D0" box="[1021,1107,446,473]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</quantity>
, Reverchon, 
<date id="FFDACFF7FFBFC835FB2BFE3BFAF122D1" box="[1252,1354,446,472]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" value="1891-07">Jul. 1891</date>
et 1892) et regno Valent. (Sierra de Castalla in rupestrib. calc., alt. 
<quantity id="4C9C44D2FFBFC835FCCDFE67FC2522F4" box="[770,926,482,509]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" unit="m" value="1600.0" valueMax="1800.0" valueMin="1400.0">1400–1800 m</quantity>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFBFC835FC66FE66FC5F22F4" authority="G. Rigo" authorityName="G. Rigo" box="[937,996,483,509]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Porta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Porta</taxonomicName>
et Rigo, 
<date id="FFDACFF7FFBFC835FB88FE67FB0922F5" box="[1095,1202,482,508]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" value="1890-07">Jul. 1890</date>
)”. The protologue also includes this information: “1879 
<superScript id="7C11447FFFBFC835FE3BFD83FDBF211D" attach="none" box="[500,516,518,532]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">ter</superScript>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFBFC835FDDCFD83FC342128" authority="Arv. Touv." authorityName="Arv. Touv." authorityYear="2021" box="[531,911,518,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elisaeanum" status="sp. n.">Hieracium Elisaeanum Arv. Touv.</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A223885EFFBFC835FC59FD82FC692128" box="[918,978,519,545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in sched. pl. exs. Reverch. Decemb. 1892 et in litt. ad Hervier (
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFBFC835FEBCFDAFFE47214D" box="[371,508,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="baeticum">H. baeticum</taxonomicName>
et flocciferum Arv. 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFBFC835FD12FDAEFD54214C" box="[733,751,555,581]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">T</collectionCode>
. prius in plant. exs. Reverch. anni 1891, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFBFC835FB7AFDAEFF622161" authority="Porta et Rigo" authorityName="Porta et Rigo" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bellidifolium">H. bellidifolium Porta et Rigo</taxonomicName>
ap. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFBFC835FEC6FDCAFE362160" authority=", Vegt." authorityName="Vegt." box="[265,397,591,617]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Porta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Porta, Vegt.</taxonomicName>
p. 44! non Scheele)”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDBE937FFBFC835FF72FDF6FABE206D" blockId="5.[136,1452,410,1085]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
We have found a specimen, herbarium sheet with barcode 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFBFC835FCF7FDF7FCFC2185" box="[824,839,626,652]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
03686242, that belong to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFBFC835FB4AFDF6FB7B2184" box="[1157,1216,627,653]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Porta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Porta</taxonomicName>
&amp; Rigo’s exsiccatum mentioned in the protologue (regno Valent., Sierra de Castalla in rupestrib. calc., alt. 
<quantity id="4C9C44D2FFBFC835FBF4FD13FB6C21B8" box="[1083,1239,662,689]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" unit="m" value="1600.0" valueMax="1800.0" valueMin="1400.0">1400–1800 m</quantity>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFBFC835FB2CFD12FAA521B8" authority="G. Rigo" authorityName="G. Rigo" box="[1251,1310,663,689]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Porta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Porta</taxonomicName>
et Rigo, 
<date id="FFDACFF7FFBFC835FA4BFD13FF7F21DD" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" value="1890-07">Jul. 1890</date>
). This sheet bears four complete and well-developed plants, and an original printed label, annotated as: “Nº. / 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFBFC835FF47FD5BFDD521F0" authority="Scheele Prodr. II." authorityName="Scheele Prodr. II." box="[136,622,734,761]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bellidifolium">Hieracium bellidifolium Scheele Prodr. II.</taxonomicName>
261. / Valentina, in rupestribus Sierra Castalla / sol. calcar. 
<quantity id="4C9C44D2FFBFC835FAE2FD5BFF182014" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" unit="m" value="1600.0" valueMax="1800.0" valueMin="1400.0">1400–1800 m</quantity>
.s.m. Jul. / 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFBFC835FED6FC86FEEF2014" authority="G. Rigo" authorityName="G. Rigo" box="[281,340,771,797]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Porta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Porta</taxonomicName>
et Rigo. iter II Hispanicum 1890” (
<figureCitation id="135FF5B2FFBFC835FD29FC87FC902015" box="[742,811,770,796]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[136,229,2028,2050]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,190,2004]" captionTargetId="figure-24@6.[196,1391,190,2004]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lectotype of Hieracium elisaeanum Arv.-Touv. ex Willk. in P (barcode P03686242) and capitula details of the specimen.— Image by courtesy of the Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle (Herbarium P), reproduced with permission" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413225/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). This specimen is therefore a 
<typeStatus id="54DF5795FFBFC835FB4AFC86FB672014" box="[1157,1244,771,797]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFBFC835FACDFC86FA1E2015" box="[1282,1445,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elisaeanum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFBFC835FACDFC86FA1E2015" box="[1282,1445,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">H. elisaeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and according to Art. 9.12 of the 
<emphasis id="B9103525FFBFC835FE36FCA2FD932048" box="[505,552,807,833]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFBFC835FE36FCA2FD932048" box="[505,552,807,833]" country="Colombia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/xsgz-nxkh" name="Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Museo de Historia Natural" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">ICN</collectionCode>
</emphasis>
, it has precedence in the 
<typeStatus id="54DF5795FFBFC835FC8DFCA3FC122049" box="[834,937,806,832]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation before the uncited specimens and the cited and not quoted illustrations that comprise the remaining original material, if such really exist.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDBE937FFBFC835FF72FCEBFF542734" blockId="5.[136,1452,410,1085]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
Fortunately, this 
<typeStatus id="54DF5795FFBFC835FEB6FCEAFE6B2080" box="[377,464,879,905]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">syntype</typeStatus>
at 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFBFC835FE3DFCEAFDBA2080" box="[498,513,879,905]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
is well preserved and complete, and shows several of the diagnostic characters used to differentiate this taxon as the apex of the rhizome with dense, long hairs, cauline leaves elliptical to ovate–lanceolate; capitula (1–)2–3; involucre 7–9(–11) mm long, with numerous stellate and few glandular hairs; achenes (1.5–) 
<quantity id="4C9C44D2FFBFC835FA9BFC33FF0F20FC" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" unit="mm" value="2.55" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.3">2.3–2.8 mm</quantity>
long, and matches the traditional concept and current use of the name (see Arvet–Touvet 1913, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFBFC835FB11FC5FFAE220FD" author="Zahn, K. H." box="[1246,1369,986,1012]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="1 - 492" refId="ref9642" refString="Zahn, K. H. (1930) Hieracium. In: Ascherson, P. &amp; Graebner, P. (Eds.) Synopsis der mitteleuropaischen Flora 12 (1). Gebruder Borntraeger, Leipzig, pp. 1 - 492." type="book chapter" year="1930">Zahn 1930</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFBFC835FAACFC5FFEB92711" author="Sell, P. D. &amp; West, C." pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="358 - 410" refId="ref9011" refString="Sell, P. D. &amp; West, C. (1976) Hieracium L. In: Tutin, T. G., Heywood, V. H., Burges, N. A., Moore, D. M., Valentine, D. H., Walters, S. M. &amp; Webb, D. A. (Eds.) Flora Europaea, vol. 4. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, pp. 358 - 410." type="book chapter" year="1976">Sell &amp; West 1976</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFBFC835FEC1FC7AFDBA2711" author="Mateo, G. &amp; Egido, F." box="[270,513,1022,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" refId="ref8422" refString="Mateo, G. &amp; Egido, F. del (2017) Estudio monografico de los generos Hieracium y Pilosella en Espana. Con referencias a Portugal y los Pirineos franceses. Monografias de Botanica Iberica, nº 20, Jolube, Jaca, 422 pp." type="book" year="2017">Mateo &amp; Egido 2017</bibRefCitation>
, Mateo 
<emphasis id="B9103525FFBFC835FD93FC7AFD352711" box="[604,654,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">et al</emphasis>
. 2017). Accordingly, we designate as the 
<typeStatus id="54DF5795FFBFC835FBA8FC7BFB752711" box="[1127,1230,1022,1048]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="B9103525FFBFC835FB3AFC7AFAAB2711" box="[1269,1296,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFBFC835FB3AFC7AFAB62711" box="[1269,1293,1023,1048]" country="Finland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15618" name="University of Helsinki" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="Herbarium">H</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
the specimen kept at 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFBFC835FF15FBA6FF512734" box="[218,234,1059,1085]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
